  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Customers may request a refund for an item or service they have already paid for, even though the ticket has not yet been closed. This article will guide you through issuing a refund while ensuring that any refunded items are correctly returned to inventory.</p><h3 id=\"Refunds:ReturnItemsBacktoInventoryandIssueaRefundonanOpenTicket-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933279378/Virtual+Cash+Terminal+VCT+Refund+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933279378\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) Refund Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933639827\" rel=\"nofollow\">Assign a Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) to Accept Payments</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154539.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Refunds:ReturnItemsBacktoInventoryandIssueaRefundonanOpenTicket-ProcessaRefundonanOpenTicket\">Process a Refund on an Open Ticket</h2><p>A VCT must be assigned to the terminal to perform a refund on a ticket.</p><p /><p>Search for the open ticket in your Ticket Queue. On the Ticket View page, click the <strong>Edit Button</strong> along the row of actions on the upper-right section of the page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154542.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154545.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h3 id=\"Refunds:ReturnItemsBacktoInventoryandIssueaRefundonanOpenTicket-RemoveandRestocktheTicketItem(s)\">Remove and Restock the Ticket Item(s)</h3><p>In the Ticket Items section of the ticket, remove the appropriate item(s) by clicking the <strong>Remove Button (X)\u00a0</strong>to the right of the item. A <strong>Remove Ticket Item</strong> pop-up will appear. Select Restock Immediately, and click <strong>Remove</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154548.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154550.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>The Ticket Totals section will now show a pending refund amount.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154553.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h3 id=\"Refunds:ReturnItemsBacktoInventoryandIssueaRefundonanOpenTicket-RefundtheTransaction\">Refund the Transaction</h3><p>On the Transaction section of the ticket, click the <strong>Refund Button</strong> under the Actions column.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Alternatively, you can click the <strong>Void Transaction Button</strong> next to the Return Button to reverse the transaction in full. If refunding a partial amount, use the <strong>Add Transaction Button</strong> on the left side of the section.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154556.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>An <strong>Add Transaction</strong> pop-up will appear. Select the refund payment method and enter the refund amount as a positive value.\u00a0Once you have entered the information and additional notes, click <strong>Submit Refund</strong>.</p><p><strong>Note:\u00a0</strong>A refund can be performed for Integrated Payments without the card being present.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154559.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Verify the transaction as posted to the ticket and that the payment has been issued back to the customer. Once the <strong>balance due is $0.00</strong>, you can <strong>Close</strong> the ticket to finalize the process.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541546/image-20230627-154603.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.22.X</p>",
